The footer contains several redirects with different links. Each button takes an url parameter to do so.

By changing the url parameter 'site' and clicking the button, the flag appears.
http://10.0.2.15/index.php?page=redirect&site=givemeyourcookie

Vulnerability:
Open Redirect vulnerabilities are a type of security vulnerability that occur when an application redirects users to an external URL without properly validating or sanitizing the URL.

Dangers:
This vulnerability allows attackers to build malicious URLs that redirect users to malicious websites potentially compromising their sensitive information or as part of phishing attacks.

Solution:
	- sanitize all URL parameters
	- only redirect to trusted websites